class MyCalendarTwo { public:     std::vector<std::vector<int>> calendar, doubleCalendar;      MyCalendarTwo() {         calendar = std::vector<std::vector<int>>();         doubleCalendar = std::vector<std::vector<int>>();     }      bool book(int start, int end) {         for (auto iter:doubleCalendar) {             if (start < iter[1] && end > iter[0])                 return false;         }         for (auto iter:calendar) {             if (end > iter[0] && start < iter[1])                 doubleCalendar.push_back({std::max(start, iter[0]), std::min(end, iter[1])});         }         calendar.push_back({start, end});         return true;     } };

fm: vector<int> dailyTemperatures(vector<int> &T) {         int n = T.size();         stack<int> s;         vector<int> ret(n, 0);         for (int i = 0; i < n; ++i) {             while (!s.empty() && T[s.top()] < T[i]) {                 ret[s.top()] = i - s.top();                 s.pop();             }             s.push(i);         }         return ret;     }
